<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation author="Curran, CH" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="33 - 89" publicationUrl="http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/handle/2246/1640?show=full" refId="B10" refString="Curran, CH, 1927. Diptera of the American Museum Congo Expedition. Part I. - Bibionidae, Bombyliidae, Dolichopodidae, Syrphidae, Trypaneidae. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 57: 33 - 89, http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/handle/2246/1640?show=full" title="Diptera of the American Museum Congo Expedition. Part I. - Bibionidae, Bombyliidae, Dolichopodidae, Syrphidae, Trypaneidae." url="http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/handle/2246/1640?show=full" volume="57" year="1927">Curran (1927)</bibRefCitation>
cites several specimens from three localities in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. In a later publication, 
<bibRefCitation author="Curran, CH" journalOrPublisher="American Museum Novitates" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 11" publicationUrl="http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/bitstream/handle/2246/2208/N1010.pdf?sequence=1" refId="B12" refString="Curran, CH, 1939. Records and descriptions of African Syrphidae III (Diptera). American Museum Novitates 1025: 1 - 11, http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/bitstream/handle/2246/2208/N1010.pdf?sequence=1" title="Records and descriptions of African Syrphidae III (Diptera)." url="http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/bitstream/handle/2246/2208/N1010.pdf?sequence=1" volume="1025" year="1939">Curran (1939)</bibRefCitation>
suggests that these specimens belong to 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. tarsatus." pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tarsatus.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. tarsatus.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M" journalOrPublisher="British Museum (Natural History), London" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/10933663" refId="B3" refString="Bezzi, M, 1915. The Syrphidae of the Ethiopian Region Based on Material in the collection of the British Museum (Natural History), with Descriptions of new Genera and Species. British Museum (Natural History), London, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/10933663" title="The Syrphidae of the Ethiopian Region Based on Material in the collection of the British Museum (Natural History), with Descriptions of new Genera and Species." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/10933663" year="1915">Bezzi (1915)</bibRefCitation>
also mentions the species from Uganda and Durban in South Africa, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Curran, CH" journalOrPublisher="American Museum Novitates" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 11" publicationUrl="http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/bitstream/handle/2246/2208/N1010.pdf?sequence=1" refId="B12" refString="Curran, CH, 1939. Records and descriptions of African Syrphidae III (Diptera). American Museum Novitates 1025: 1 - 11, http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/bitstream/handle/2246/2208/N1010.pdf?sequence=1" title="Records and descriptions of African Syrphidae III (Diptera)." url="http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/bitstream/handle/2246/2208/N1010.pdf?sequence=1" volume="1025" year="1939">Curran (1939)</bibRefCitation>
also considers these specimens as 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. tarsatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tarsatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. tarsatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We have not encountered females that could be associated with the male of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. ingratus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ingratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. ingratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. No DNA barcodes are available for 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. ingratus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ingratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. ingratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
